<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Well:<P>Crowd Control rolls down to experience like most things but at your level your spell line up should probably look like ...<P>Stun<BR>Stun<BR>AOE Mezz<BR>Mezz<BR>Tash<BR>Root<BR>Charm<BR>Buff Slot<P>I had GREAT success playing the charm game in HH, but you might want to avoid the added headache until you get crowd control down.  <P>I constantly hammer my 2 stun hotkeys as I attempt to control the pull, used AOE mezz on anything more than a pull of 3.<P>Bind your target nearest opponent key to something easier to hit (I use the ~ key myself).<P>Until you get used to dealing with single target mezz (and you should try to get used to it) use AOE mezz.  The downside to AOE mezz is that when it wears off you are going to get pummeled quickly.  This is where root comes in.  AOE mezz the pull then single target root them, when AOE mezz breaks you single target mezz them.  This rooting saves you from getting jumped all at once and teachs you how to target which is what you will need to learn to single target mezz.<P>Eventually you will want to move from AOE mezz to single target mezz for most pulls.  Generally I get one mezzed as the mobs start heading towards the group.  Then you run into the middle of the mess and start using your stuns:<BR>short stun, long stun, single target mezz ... repeat.<P>--------------------<P><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=65288" TARGET=_blank>Sage Zanithar TideBreaker</A><BR>Phantasmist <BR>The Relentless, Cazic Thule
</FONT>
