<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
My spell lineup typically goes like this:<P>tash<BR>slow<BR>big nuke<BR>root<BR>single target mez<BR>memory blur<BR>speed<BR>breeze<P>Typical routine:  mez everything but the mob the puller is fighting, one by one.  Once they're mezzed, debuff the one that's still fighting, then the others. If mez is still holding when the first one dies, memory blur before they break it (keeps it from rushing you or the cleric).  Then remez others, and so on.<P>Sometimes I keep aoe mez up instead of root, but I use it only in serious emergencies - I've found it causes more problems for me than it solves.  One - it's hard to judge how to keep yourself out of the area of effect.  Two - it breaks quickly, and all the mobs that aren't currently being fought will rush you.  I never use stuns, although I'm rare in that regard, I've found.<P>Pretty much it's a matter of experimentation until you find what works for you.<P>Edited to add - the last two slots are swap slots.  Often switched for other buffs/charm/gate depending on the situation.<P>--------------------<P><A HREF="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=73730" TARGET=_blank>Teraine Mindsifter</A>, 54 Illusionist<BR><A HREF="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=102562" TARGET=_blank>Gisselle S'Haine</A>, 40 Shadow Knight<BR>of <A HREF="http://www.povarpta.org" TARGET=_blank>Povar Tarew Alliance</A>, Xev
</FONT>
