Unfortunately, at 17 you are not going to have the ideal setup, which is very very similar to what zanithar said.<P>That is the general "crowd control" setup enchanters tend to use when they are going dungeon diving, or someplace where they arent quite sure what is going on.<P>The second posters Spell line up might work for them, but it is not one i would reccomend at all. It has a memblur spell, and 2 buffs as standard.  Keeping buffs memmed is a habit to get out of, since at higher levels you simply cant afford the spell slots.<P>I would reccomend somthing like ...<P>Charm<BR>Tash<BR>Stun ( flux )<BR>Root<BR>Single mez<BR>AoE mez<BR>Nuke<BR>slow / Haste / Breeze ( we call this one a buff slot )<P>This will be close enough to what you will have memmed at higher levels to give you a good feel for it.  If you are in Full crowd control mode, lose the nuke at level 20, and put your research stun there ( color shift ).<P>Organize your spellbook so that spells you will have to sit and swap in and out are close to each other ( haste, slow , breeze , gate ).<P>Practice keeping your mana high, since you are ( or will become ) the "saftey net" for your group.  Do your crowd control, keep breeze / haste up, and nuke if you have left over mana.  Eventually, you will nuke less and less as you find it agros more than you want ( thats for much later tho ).<P>Set up some hotkeys to announce to your group important things like " this is charmed ", so they understand why they cant hit it.  Make a bank of pet commands to switch to when you charm something.<P>Try using root instead of memblur, even tho memblur works ok at your level.  Mez itself has a decent memblur till you hit the mid to late 20s.<P><BR>Good Luck, and have fun  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>Llorian<BR>56 Enchanter
</FONT>
