<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Lot's of good advice coming from all of the folks here, so I don't have much to add regarding spell line-up or tactics. I would suggest that you keep in mind an enchanters flexibility while grouped (and even solo, to a lesser extent) and then build a process that works well for you.<P>Being able to be "your own enchanter" in your approach to various situations is one of the better things about our class. We get a little breathing room to be creative!   <IMG SRC="cool.gif" border="0"> <P>I have noticed a very definite drift to "support class" role as I got to about level 45ish, and I assume that most other folks have too. That may be because there seem to be few +50 enchanters running around and there are almost none in the alliance of guilds (CoN, TIK, and CU on Bristlebane) that I hang out with. It is not really that uncommon for me to be buffing 2 groups and then the obligitory mob debuffing... I don't think that I have stunned, nuked, or charmed (except once by accident, DOH!) a mob in months.<P>Hunt well, and have a great time playing your enchanter!<P>Niz<P>--------------------<P>Nizudn Mindfear 52 Enchanter<BR>Nizuln Sharpfang 49 Druid<P>Chosen of the Nameless<BR>Bristlebane
