<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Single most useful tactic I've ever been given on casting:<P>If you've moved but want to cast immediately after you've stopped - use a direction key to turn slightly before casting.<P>At higher levels this may be less important when you might be able to channel a spell through. But I find moving still has more chance of interrupting my spell than being hit by a mob unless it triple/quad hits in the time I'm casting.<P>What I often do if there's room is to use the shortest duration AE stun, back up or run past a few feet and turn just as the recast delay goes, so I can hit the mez button immediately and have a slight distance for the mob to travel before it can hit me.<P>I know this is a basic tactic - probably in a guide somewhere or something most people pick up. Just haven't seen it printed in a while.<P><BR>Belain Laufey<BR>56 Beguiler<BR>Prexus
</FONT>
