Sort of on this topic: If more than one MOB is pulled, should the group attack the strongest one (so I would have to mez all the weaker ones for a longer amount of time, thus using more mana to re-cast mez on all of them), or should it attack the weakest one (so I would mez all the stronger ones, thus increasing the chance of a resist)?  I thought that they should attack the weakest ones to get them out of the way more quickly, but one guy (the puller, I believe =) said that wouldn't be good, since the stronger ones would resist too much.  This was my first real mezzing experience (and he said something about having an enchanter, so he knows the tactics) so I didn't argue with him.   <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0">  Does everyone here agree with him?
