My typical spell lineup for grouping is:<P>Breeze/swap<BR>Quick/swap<BR>Tash<BR>Slow<BR>short stun<BR>long stun<BR>AoE mez<BR>single mez<P>I am also one of those AoE Mez lovers and will either recast as needed (and remind folks to taunt before breaking mez) or stun/mez when it breaks. I should probably switch to rooting the mezzed ones; thanks for the tip! Note that if the crowd to be controlled is adds, not big pulls, I will single mez them as they come in.<P>The recast time on mem blur is outrageous and my CHA isn't to the point I feel comfortable charming; I should be addressing that soon, though.<P>As others have said, find a style that works for you and practice it.<P>Luthian - 28th level bossy Enchantress<BR>Xev<P>--------------------<P>Luthian - 54th level Bossy Illusionist<BR>Xev
