<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
What is this "long stun" everyone is talking about?  If it is color shift he does not get it till level 20.  Or did I miss a stun spell along the way?<P>Llorian pretty hit on what I did at that level.<P>Another thing you can start learning now is mana management.  The use of Languid Pace and Quickness are the 2 you will use for now.<BR>You will burn a lot of mana if you are casting Quickness on all your tanks plus a Languid Pace for each mob.  If your group is tank heavy (3 or more) I would say skip Quickness and just go with Languid Pace, or maybe just Quickness whichever tank is the main damage shield (will help him build agro).  <P>Mana management will be your ongoing struggle. Soon you will be required to Slow mobs, Haste Tanks, Clarity casters, and keep yourself about 80% mana so you are fully prepared to deal with that 5-6 pull. Learn to time buffs and stagger them so you won't get hit with the whole group asking for crack and haste at the same time.<P>On that note with single pulls, throw in a Tash and a Languid Pace and then med thru.  You have now lowered the mobs magic resistance (this saving every caster some mana from lest resists) and have reduced the mobs damage output by about 25%.  You have earned the right to med up.  The group will be much better off with you fully prepared to put a stop to those mass pulls than they would be with you helping on single pulls.<P>Zandoff<BR>32 Enchanter Karana
</FONT>
