Unless mistaken, I believe my News page states the guide is being rewritten; I'm condensing most of the Circles info into Tactics sections, then I'll be going back through the Circles pages and weeding out a lot of stuff that was better suited to the general tactics.  I want to focus on changes to tactics at that level, not restating the same information over and over like the guide does now.<P>At the time I wrote about charming in the 5th Circle, I found my charms were lasting just fine, I was just young and dumb.  My second enchanter charm solos with 85 CHA at the moment, in full cloth armor.  Only problem I really have is not having auto-med, which makes charm soloing a bit more annoying to me; but that's about it.<P>I apologize for the Circles that are out of date, it's why the rewrite is happening.  Unfortunately, I work full time, and have two characters I play a lot, plus I'm on the board here when I should be updating.<P>For the record, the Circles info shouldn't be taken over something stated in the growing tactics sections (I'm in Groups right now).  Once I finish with Tactics, I'll revise the Circles (won't take long) then start on Quests, Jeweling, and finally Stories.  With the ton of requests for "Where to Level" I might add that, but I'm really against it, the purpose of my guide was to teach <I>how</I> to enchant no matter where you go.<P>I don't think high CHA hurts, but I don't go nuts for it anymore.<P>--------------------<P><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=147058" TARGET=_blank>Sorikk</A> Iksar Master<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=41820" TARGET=_blank>Xornn Mier`noen</A> High Elf Beguiler<P><A HREF="http://members.tripod.com/xornn" TARGET=_blank>Xornn's Guide to Enchanting</A>
